The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to strings and covers, which are typical topics in computer science subfields such as data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The focus on linear time algorithms suggests that the paper may be more likely to belong to cs.DS or cs.CC, but the use of combinatorial and geometric concepts also makes cs.DM and cs.CG plausible categories. The mention of a by-product algorithm for checking the length of the shortest seed suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.SI, which deals with social and information networks and their algorithms.
